parameters:
Will we escape to the magical city of
Vaal?

Zerachiel: Just to be safe, it might be
better to prepare...

Sariel: It was unexpected for Remiel to
lose. You did your best.
Sariel: That's why, it's a shame...

Sariel: If only you didn't have a heart,
Eden-sama would have been delighted to
have you as a perfect weapon.

Sariel: Ahaha, the preparations are more
than enough, right?

Sariel: We had to interrupt in Logress,
but...

Sariel: Shall we begin a delightful
killing spree?

Sariel: After coming this far, refusing
is unfair, isn't it!?

Zerachiel: It's true that I am a
homunculus, and there are similarities
between us...

Zerachiel: I am just living the present
to the fullest as Zerachiel.

Zerachiel: You, who seeks pleasure in
killing each other, are a completely
different existence from me.
Zerachiel: I am not a weapon.

Sariel: ...That's a cruel way of
speaking.

Sariel: I'll do anything if it's for the
sake of Eden-sama.

Sariel: It was certainly tough at first,
but the battlefield is where I shine the
most. I receive praise and it's
incredibly fun.

Zerachiel: Certainly, in the past, I
didn't have any special emotions about
taking the lives of targets.

Zerachiel: I was happy to receive praise
from Eden, and I was willing to do
anything for them.

Zerachiel: In that sense, maybe I was
just like you all.

Zerachiel: Taking unnecessary lives is
wrong. I shouldn't enjoy it.

Sariel: Oh, how pitiful that you can't
experience the pleasure of taking lives.

Zerachiel: Sariel, do you understand
what you have done?

Sariel: It's not a big deal. It doesn't
matter to me how many humans die.

Sariel: I don't have any interest, so I
don't think it's bad.

Zerachiel: I thought you would say that.
So...

Zerachiel: Sariel, I'll make it clear to
you.
Zerachiel: I don't want to fight you.

Zerachiel: Until I came to Logres... I
thought it wouldn't matter if I died at
any time.

Zerachiel: No, I've never even been
aware of a future where I would die.
Zerachiel: But... I want to live.

Zerachiel: I want to live and spend
peaceful days together with everyone who
has accepted me.

Zerachiel: Sariel... Let's stop doing
bad things.

Zerachiel: You're just being deceived by
Eden.

Sariel: It's like I'm being lectured.
It's annoying.

Sariel: Well then... I'll let you see my
true power.

Sariel: Zerachiel, you are an impostor
of mine.

Sariel: How dare you lecture me, even
though you're just a fake? It's beyond
rude, isn't it?

Sariel: If you have important people
like that, then I'll destroy every
single one of them for you.

Sariel: In order to deliver the moment
when you cry and beg for your life... to
you.
Sariel: Ahaha, did I make you angry?

Sariel: It's best for impostors to
despair until they lose all emotions.

Sariel: I, Sariel-sama, will also break
Zerachiel's heart.

Sariel: Ah, my emotions are rising...
I'm so glad I met you...!!
Zerachiel: So this is how it ends...!

Zerachiel: Geez, what a troublesome
original you are!

Sariel: Kyahaha! Can you keep up with my
moves...?

Sariel: If you don't want to die,
then...!!
Zerachiel: Lulu!? Why are you here!?

Lulu: Hmm, I've been waiting because I
was worried about you.
Lulu: You need an item, right?
I want to modify my equipment
Lulu: Just a little more, hang in there.
Lulu: You need an item, right?
I want to modify my equipment
Lulu: Just a little more, hang in there.
